[3] Response
- Sat 17 Aug 2019. South Kivu meeting
[7 sur 7 in French, machine trans., edited]
https://7sur7.cd/2019/08/17/ebola-au-sud-kivu-une-reunion-urgente-convoquee-ce-samedi
[byline: Isaac Musharhamina]

After the confirmed case of Ebola in South Kivu province, 100 km [about 62 mi] from the city of Bukavu, the Provincial Health Inspectorate announces that 2 helicopters from Goma landed in Chowe with a team of caregivers and medicines to strengthen the teams already in place.

This [Sat 17 Aug 2019], an emergency meeting will be held in Bukavu with the national level. On the other hand, the doctor Claude Bahizire, in charge of communication of the provincial inspection of the Health of South Kivu, calls the population to the respects of the hygienic norms. "We ask all families to observe the universal rules of hygiene, especially washing hands with soap or chlorinated water every time, which is very serious," insisted Claude Bahizirhe.

Note that in their game bags, there are vaccines and additional staff for good care.

