- Mon 19 Aug 2019
[Radio Okapi, machine transl., abridged, edited]
https://www.radiookapi.net/2019/08/19/actualite/sante/nord-kivu-liccn-installe-des-points-de-controle-pour-prevenir-ebola-dans

The Congolese Institute for the Conservation of Nature (ICCN) installed [on Sat 17 Aug 2019] at least 3 checkpoints and prevention against Ebola virus disease in the Virunga National Park.

Without providing figures, the ICCN's director of communication for Virunga National Park, Wenga Mulayi lamented a slight decline in the number of tourists visiting the park, since the announcement of the 1st Ebola case in the city of Goma and the declaration of the epidemic as a global health emergency. This, for him, constitutes a shortfall for the ICCN, but also for the country.

The 1st checkpoint at Rwindi Bridge on the Goma-Butembo axis in Rutshuru territory is already operational. The other 2 are being installed at the Semuliki bridge and Kambo ferry in the Beni territory, towards the border with Uganda, said Joel Wenga Mulayi, ICCN's director of communication for the Virunga National Park. According to him, by this project against the Ebola virus disease, the ICCN aims to contribute to the safety of travelers who cross the park, by monitoring their health.

Devices at these checkpoints include temperature testing, handwashing, but also passenger registration for a data bank, when needed.

